---
import { SAINTS } from "../lib/data";
import {
  AMERICA_MOVEMENT_I,
  AMERICA_MOVEMENT_II,
  AMERICA_AWAITING,
  findAmerican,
} from "../lib/america";
import { withBase } from "../lib/format";
import { saintAvatar } from "../lib/icons";
import DomeMark from "./icons/DomeMark.astro";
import ByzCross from "./icons/ByzCross.astro";

const movement1 = AMERICA_MOVEMENT_I.map((s) => ({
  s,
  hit: findAmerican(SAINTS, s.name, s.epithet),
  catSlug: "t-" + s.cat.toLowerCase().replace(/[^a-z]+/g, "-"),
}));

const movement2 = AMERICA_MOVEMENT_II.map((s) => ({
  s,
  hit: findAmerican(SAINTS, s.name, s.epithet),
  catSlug: "t-" + s.cat.toLowerCase().replace(/[^a-z]+/g, "-"),
}));

const awaiting = AMERICA_AWAITING.map((s) => ({
  s,
  reposed: s.reposedYear || (s.years.split("–").pop() || "").trim(),
}));
---

<section class="am-hero">
  <div class="dome-bg"><DomeMark w={460} color="var(--byz)" /></div>
  <div class="inner">
    <div class="eyebrow">The Holy People of America</div>
    <h1>The Saints of America</h1>
    <p class="am-hero-tagline">A Pilgrimage of Hope</p>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="am-essay">
  <div class="am-essay-inner">
    <h2 class="am-essay-head">The Holy People of America</h2>
    <p>
      When first approaching Orthodoxy, it can seem as if it is far away. You
      might wonder: Where has the Church been this whole time? Why does America
      feel as though it has been left to wander in the desert?
    </p>
    <p>
      The thing is, the Church has been here all along. Some might say she has
      existed since before the foundations of the world. America, on the other
      hand, is young. Though the Church has grown slowly here, she is here.
    </p>
    <blockquote class="am-pullquote">
      <p>
        "The kingdom of heaven is like leaven that a woman took and hid in
        three measures of flour, till it was all leavened."
      </p>
      <cite>— Matthew 13:33</cite>
    </blockquote>
    <p>
      Slowly, and often hidden from the world, Christ has been planting seeds
      of holiness in this land. The holy people of America remind us that
      Orthodoxy is not only something ancient and far away. It is alive here.
      Saints crossed oceans, endured loneliness, built churches, prayed in
      wilderness places, served the poor, and healed the wounded.
    </p>
    <p>Many of them never saw the fruits of their labor. They planted, and God gave the increase.</p>
    <p>
      On this page you will find a small gathering of witnesses — canonized
      saints, righteous elders, missionaries, monastics, martyrs, mothers,
      priests, and faithful servants whose lives show that God is still working
      in this land.
    </p>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="am-section">
  <div class="am-movement-head">
    <div class="eyebrow">Movement I</div>
    <h2>They Came from Across the Sea</h2>
    <p class="am-movement-tagline">
      They left the old world behind — crossing oceans into loneliness — to
      carry the faith to a continent that did not yet know it.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="am-grid">
    {
      movement1.map(({ s, hit, catSlug }) => {
        const Tag = hit ? "a" : "div";
        return (
          <Tag
            class={`am-card${hit ? " clickable" : ""}`}
            data-saint={hit?.id}
            href={hit ? withBase(`saint/${hit.id}`) : undefined}
          >
            <div
              class="portrait"
              set:html={saintAvatar({ name: s.name }, 88, 108, {
                type: s.cat,
              })}
            />
            <div class="body">
              <div class="card-head">
                <h3>{s.name}</h3>
                <span class="years">{s.years}</span>
              </div>
              <div class="epithet">{s.epithet}</div>
              <span class={`tag ${catSlug}`}>
                <i />
                {s.cat}
              </span>
              <p>{s.contribution}</p>
              <div class="card-foot">
                <span class="feast">Feast · {s.feast}</span>
                <span class="glor">Glorified {s.glorified}</span>
              </div>
            </div>
          </Tag>
        );
      })
    }
  </div>

  <div class="am-movement-head am-movement-head--ii">
    <div class="eyebrow">Movement II</div>
    <h2>Those Born of This Land</h2>
    <p class="am-movement-tagline">
      The first fruits of Orthodoxy native to this soil — children of Alaska
      and America who became holy where they were born.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="am-grid">
    {
      movement2.map(({ s, hit, catSlug }) => {
        const Tag = hit ? "a" : "div";
        return (
          <Tag
            class={`am-card${hit ? " clickable" : ""}`}
            data-saint={hit?.id}
            href={hit ? withBase(`saint/${hit.id}`) : undefined}
          >
            <div
              class="portrait"
              set:html={saintAvatar({ name: s.name }, 88, 108, {
                type: s.cat,
              })}
            />
            <div class="body">
              <div class="card-head">
                <h3>{s.name}</h3>
                <span class="years">{s.years}</span>
              </div>
              <div class="epithet">{s.epithet}</div>
              <span class={`tag ${catSlug}`}>
                <i />
                {s.cat}
              </span>
              <p>{s.contribution}</p>
              <div class="card-foot">
                <span class="feast">Feast · {s.feast}</span>
                <span class="glor">Glorified {s.glorified}</span>
              </div>
            </div>
          </Tag>
        );
      })
    }
  </div>

  <div class="am-awaiting">
    <div class="panel">
      <div class="note">
        <ByzCross size={22} color="var(--gold-deep)" />
        <div>
          <div class="eyebrow" style="margin-bottom:8px">
            Awaiting Glorification
          </div>
          <h2>A Living Church Still Growing</h2>
          <p>
            The work is not finished. These reposed servants are held in living
            memory by the faithful — remembered with love, though not yet
            formally glorified by the Church.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="pair">
        {
          awaiting.map(({ s, reposed }) => (
            <div class="am-await-card">
              <div
                class="portrait-await"
                set:html={saintAvatar({ name: s.name }, 108, 132, {
                  awaiting: true,
                })}
              />
              <div>
                <div class="head">
                  <h3>{s.name}</h3>
                  {s.years && <span class="years">{s.years}</span>}
                </div>
                <div class="epithet">{s.epithet}</div>
                <div class="badges">
                  <span class="tag t-venerated">
                    <i />
                    {s.role}
                  </span>
                  <span class="tag t-venerated">Not yet glorified</span>
                </div>
                <p>{s.contribution}</p>
                <div class="repose">
                  ✝{reposed ? ` Reposed ${reposed} · ` : " "}{s.place}
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          ))
        }
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="am-closing">
  <div class="am-closing-inner">
    <div class="eyebrow">For the Lonely Convert</div>
    <p>
      Now you join their ranks. Let your mustard seed take root, that through
      God's grace one more person might find truth, comfort, and refuge beneath
      the wings of our Father.
    </p>
    <p>
      The very fact that you are here is evidence that the seeds they planted
      have borne fruit.
    </p>
  </div>
</section>
